players.name: Pete Rose
players.description: 1969 Topps Deckle Edge Pete Rose. This set consists of 33 cards, each measuring 2-1/4 by 3-1/4 inches, that were inserted into packs of the 1969 regular issue. The set derives its name from the scalloped edges.

players.name: Cal Ripken
players.description: 1982 Topps Cal Ripken Rookie card. The 1982 Topps set consists of 792 cards measuring 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches. At the time, this set marked Topps' largest set offering.

players.name: Hank Aaron
players.description: 1962 Post Cereal Hank Aaron. This set consists of 200 cards cut from the back of cereal boxes and measure 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches. Some of the cards can be very scarce.

players.name: Willie McCovey
players.description: 1969 Topps Deckle Edge Willie McCovey. This set consists of 33 cards, each measuring 2-1/4 by 3-1/4 inches, that were inserted into packs of the 1969 regular issue. The set derives its name from the scalloped edges.

players.name: O.J. Simpson
players.description: 1970 Topps Football O.J. Simpson. The set consists of 263 cards, each measuring 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches. This is OJ's rookie card. He had a very slashing running style.

players.name: Sandy Koufax
players.description: 1966 Topps Sandy Koufax. This was Sandy's last card, since he retired after the 1966 season. The set consists of 598 cards, each measuring 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches.

players.name: Juan Marichal
players.description: 1971 Topps Juan Marichal. The set consists of 752 cards and measure 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches. The black border is especially susceptible to chipping and wear, thus PSA mint value 10's are rare.

players.name: Barry Bonds
players.description: 1986 Topps Traded Barry Bonds. This is Bonds' rookie card. The set consists of 132 cards, and was only available as a complete set. They measure the usual 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches.

players.name: Willie Mays
players.description: 1960 Topps All Star Willie Mays. This set is a subset of 22 cards that highlight top players and were released at the end of the regular set numbering 551-572. For the first time, Topps issued a horizontal design for the entire set.

players.name: Joe Morgan
players.description: 1973 Topps Joe Morgan. This set consists of 660 cards and measure 2-1/2 by 3-1/2 inches. It was the last set issued in a mult-series format.
